narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It's a language course, and if you're looking at L3 then chances are you're taking it to fill requirements. It will fill your requirements. Why are you reading this evaluation again?
If you have never taken Spanish before and aren't very good at languages, don't use Spanish to fulfill your requirement. It's unnecessarily difficult.
I recommend this class because it appears less difficult to other L3 languages.
Yes, take the class following 110 and 120 for it will not only solidify, but also expand your understanding, writing, and speaking ability in Spanish.
Yes, if you are fulfilling a language requirement. I also feel that I got the most out of this level Spanish after taking I and II.
If you have to take L3, take it with Juan Pablo. He is great.
I would recommend this course to a fellow student.
